  128. ‌let rec instr_iter f i =
  129.   match i.desc with
  130.     Iend -> ()
  131.   | _ ->
  132.       f i;
  133.       match i.desc with
  134.         Iend -> ()
  135.       | Ireturn | Iop Itailcall_ind | Iop(Itailcall_imm _) -> ()
  136.       | Iifthenelse(_tst, ifso, ifnot) ->
  137.           instr_iter f ifso; instr_iter f ifnot; instr_iter f i.next
  138.       | Iswitch(_index, cases) ->
  139.           for i = 0 to Array.length cases - 1 do
  140.             instr_iter f cases.(i)
  141.           done;
  142.           instr_iter f i.next
  143.       | Icatch(_, handlers, body) ->
  144.           instr_iter f body;
  145.           List.iter (fun (_n, handler) -> instr_iter f handler) handlers;
  146.           instr_iter f i.next
  147.       | Iexit _ -> ()
  148.       | Itrywith(body, handler) ->
  149.           instr_iter f body; instr_iter f handler; instr_iter f i.next
  150.       | Iraise _ -> ()
  151.       | _ ->
  152.           instr_iter f i.next

  154. ‌let operation_is_pure = function
  155.   | Icall_ind | Icall_imm _ | Itailcall_ind | Itailcall_imm _
  156.   | Iextcall _ | Istackoffset _ | Istore _ | Ialloc _ | Ipoll _
  157.   | Idls_get
  158.   | Iintop(Icheckbound) | Iintop_imm(Icheckbound, _) | Iopaque -> false
  159.   | Ispecific sop -> Arch.operation_is_pure sop
  160.   | _ -> true

  162. ‌let operation_can_raise op =
  163.   match op with
  164.   | Icall_ind | Icall_imm _ | Iextcall _
  165.   | Iintop (Icheckbound) | Iintop_imm (Icheckbound, _)
  166.   | Ialloc _ | Ipoll _ -> true
  167.   | Ispecific sop -> Arch.operation_can_raise sop
  168.   | _ -> false
